<br>
First of all, if your friend is any good, he's likely going to use ranged attacks if you do nothing but run and try and pet kite him. In the relatively confined area of an arena, and little to no cover to break his LOS with arrows, he'll eventually likely kill you before your air pet kills him assuming he has any bow that's 30 damage or more, some decent archery skill and some half decent arrows.<br>
<br>
Second, against a warrior's innate MR, it's unlikely that you're going to land a malosini or at least, he's not gonna let you stand still and chain cast it on him until it does. If you had Mala, that'd be a huge help, but you're a level away still.<br>
<br>
As for the earth pet, unless it's the 65 earth pet, again, you're not gonna stick a root on him, and even if it does land, without significant debuffing, it's not gonna stick for but a second or two, not giving you the time you need to cast a big nuke. As others have said, you're likely going to have to stick to scars.<br>
<br>
Definitely have SOW. Definitely pray he doesn't have SOW. Definitely use some pet kiting to wear him down a bit. Definitely try annul magicing him as an opening gambit (before you sic the pet, or it could poof due to the annul bug and pets). Get rid of his SOW and/or hp buffs/resist buffs and that can drastically up your chances of succcess.<br>
<br>
I'm assuming you don't have your epic? If you did, the fight would be entirely different. You'd shred him and he'd get a few stuns from bashes/kicks from behind.  Barring that, I'd actually use the water pet (the 54 even if you need to). If it's velocitied, the backstab while you're pet kiting him is important and the cold nuke will land for at least partial almost every time (as opposed to the air stun which is going to be resisted tons).<br>
<br>
